<br>
The converse to the question 'Why do you care if someone inspects you without asking' is 'Why is it so difficult to ask'. Asking is a sign of respect and immediately begins the relationship (no matter how short term it may be) in a friendly and civilized way. Treating others with respect generally means you get treated with respect in return. Being consistently courtesous and respectful of others is what ultimately earns you a good reputation which is extremely important on a small close-knit server like this one. It is odd that so many don't realize this since it seems like such a common sense thing.<br>
<br>
Coriolis of Erudin, Firiona Vie, Beguiler<br>
